/*
 * HapticServer.cpp
 * ================
 * SERVER side – runs on PC-A (has Novint Falcon #1).
 *
 * What this does:
 *   1. Reads position from local Falcon at 1 kHz
 *   2. Sends HapticPacket UDP to CLIENT_IP:4000 (if TX enabled)
 *   3. Listens on 0.0.0.0:4000 for HapticPacket from client
 *   4. Optionally applies received client force to local Falcon
 *   5. Shows TWO candlestick charts side by side:
 *        LEFT  = local haptic data  (what THIS Falcon is doing, SENT)
 *        RIGHT = remote haptic data (what CLIENT Falcon is doing, RECEIVED)
 *   6. Info panel: local x/y/z/mag, remote x/y/z/mag, net stats
 *
 * Controls:
 *   T       Toggle sending data to client  (TX on/off)
 *   R       Toggle receiving from client   (RX on/off)
 *   F       Toggle force feedback to local Falcon from received data
 *   +/-     Step candle window (1ms–1000ms)
 *   [       1 ms window  (1000 bars/s max)
 *   ]       1000 ms window (1 bar/s min)
 *   N       Toggle network entirely
 *   ESC     Quit
 *
 * Wire protocol (UDP port 4000, same struct both directions):
 *   double  ts      8 bytes  ms since sender start
 *   float   x       4 bytes  metres
 *   float   y       4 bytes  metres
 *   float   z       4 bytes  metres
 *   float   mag     4 bytes  metres
 *   float   fx      4 bytes  force X  N  (0 if no feedback)
 *   float   fy      4 bytes  force Y  N
 *   float   fz      4 bytes  force Z  N
 *   uint8   btn     1 byte   button bitmask
 *   uint8   flags   1 byte   bit0=hasFeedback
 *   ── total: 38 bytes ──
 *
 * Build: drop into CHAI3D GLFW example folder, replace existing .cpp.
 * Extra dep: ws2_32.lib  (added via #pragma comment below)
 *
 * Set CLIENT_IP at the top of this file before building.
 * The server's own IP is detected at runtime and shown in the console + HUD.
 */

